events.name: Golden State Warriors at Orlando Magic

headlines.description: — Nikola Vucevic had 30 points, 16 rebounds and 10 assists for his third career triple-double and the Orlando Magic overcame a 13-point, fourth-quarter deficit to beat the Golden State Warriors 124-120 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Vucevic has triple-double, Magic rally to beat Warriors

headlines.description: — Jamal Murray scored a career-high 50 points, All-Star starter Nikola Jokic had a triple-double and the Denver Nuggets adjusted to a schedule change by handing the Cleveland Cavaliers their ninth straight loss, 120-103 on Friday night in a matchup...
headlines.shortLinkText: Murray's 50 points power Nuggets past crumbling Cavaliers

headlines.description: — All-Star Joel Embiid scored a career-high 50 points to lead the Philadelphia 76ers to a 112-105 victory over the Chicago Bulls on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Embiid scores career-high 50 points to lead 76ers past Bulls

headlines.description: — Kemba Walker scored a season-high 28 points  and the Boston Celtics held off the Atlanta Hawks 121-109 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Kemba Walker scores 28 in return, Celtics down Hawks 121-109

headlines.description: — Ja Morant scored 21 of his 29 points in the second half, Jonas Valanciunas added 17 points and 15 rebounds and the Memphis Grizzlies rallied down the stretch for a 109-95 victory over the Detroit Pistons on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Morant leads Grizzlies in late rally to defeat Detroit

events.name: Oklahoma City Thunder at Milwaukee Bucks

headlines.description: — Giannis Antetokounmpo had 29 points, a season-high 19 rebounds and eight assists, and the Milwaukee Bucks beat the Oklahoma City Thunder 98-85 on Friday night to snap a five-game skid.
headlines.shortLinkText: Bucks snap 5-game skid with 98-85 victory over Thunder

events.name: Phoenix Suns at New Orleans Pelicans

headlines.description: — Chris Paul had 15 points and a season-high 19 assists, spearheading an 11-point, fourth-quarter comeback by the Phoenix Suns in a 132-114 victory over the New Orleans Pelicans on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Paul has 19 assists, Suns rally to beat Pelicans 132-114

headlines.description: — Norman Powell scored a season-high 31 points and the Toronto Raptors beat the Minnesota Timberwolves 86-81 on Friday night, closing the game with an 11-0 run.
headlines.shortLinkText: Raptors score last 11 to defeat Timberwolves 86-81

headlines.description: — Kawhi Leonard scored 29 points, reserve Lou Williams had 19 and the Los Angeles Clippers edged Utah 116-112 on Friday night, snapping the Jazz's nine-game winning streak.
headlines.shortLinkText: Clippers edge Jazz 116-112, snap Utah's 9-game win streak
